Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and normal blood glucose. These findings suggest significant renal dysfunction, likely with impaired filtration and possible tubular damage. The low HbA1c excludes chronic hyperglycemia. Urine abnormalities (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) further support renal pathology. Prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended to clarify etiology and guide management.
